cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.COM, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the use of mmWave spectrum for cellular networks and proposes a sharing mechanism among cellular operators. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of Licensed Spectrum Access (LSA) to coordinate sharing among cellular operators. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a possible category as the paper may discuss security concerns related to spectrum sharing. 
- cs.COM (Computers and Society) is a possible category as the paper may discuss the societal impact of efficient spectrum sharing in 5G cellular scenarios. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper may discuss the use of mmWave spectrum for multimedia applications in 5G cellular scenarios.
